GE Oil & Gas opened a new facility in Takoradi Port, Ghana. The Tarkodi service facility expands GE's global footprint with a new Sub Saharan Africa facility to support customer operations, delivering more than 45,000 training hours for Ghanaian personnel over the next five years, as it seeks to build a world-class team locally. Read more. More on GE in Africa in this BRIEFING.&nbsp;